<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-20T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-20T22:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">853B.20/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-20T23:00:00-04:00">April 20,
                                    1942—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>416. Your 305, April 10, 4 p.m. The Department continues in doubt as to
                            whether the Portuguese Government has taken any steps to correct the
                            situation referred to in this correspondence. It is urgent that this
                            matter be clarified without further delay. You are accordingly requested
                            to obtain from the Foreign Office a definite reply at once, reporting to
                            the Department the precise nature of steps taken.</p>
                        <p>It is not clear from your telegram that the Legation is keeping the
                            Consulate in Horta advised of developments, as requested in the
                            Department’s 319, March 31, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>